data.title: Cher
data.meta_description: Read all about Cher with TV Guide's exclusive biography including their list of awards, celeb facts and more at TV Guide.
data.text:
Fast Facts

Met future singing partner and husband Sonny Bono in a Sunset Boulevard coffee shop in 1962; when they first began to sing together, they called themselves Caesar and Cleo

Was a backup singer for Phil Spector-produced groups like the Ronettes and the Crystals in the mid-1960s

Is one of five actor-singers to have had a No

1 single and won an acting Academy Award

(The others are Frank Sinatra, Bing Crosby, Barbra Streisand and Jamie Foxx

) Has had a No

1 single in each of the last six decades, beginning with the 1965 Sonny Bono duet "I Got You Babe

"
